{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Review input is scoped to changed lines only, not full modified files.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is typically at a module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder), not just a single pure function. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess is required; fixture diffs are sufficient. LLM-DEP: correctness is about selected line ranges, not model judgment. REJECTION-GATE: rejected System because behavior text does not require a real PR/API call; rejected Agentic/Workflow because behavior text is scoping input, not model output quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Wire diff extraction and input-construction modules together using realistic unified-diff fixtures for multi-hunk/multi-file PRs; assert only changed hunks are included and unchanged file content is excluded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the PR diff view.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: this depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and API validation (line/side/commit context). MOCK-HIDE: mocked clients often accept invalid position payloads that GitHub rejects or remaps. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Integration because behavior text explicitly targets correctness in the real PR diff view.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions and verify via API/UI fields that each comment lands on the intended changed line in the diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Agent identifies at least one real defect in a PR containing a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justifica